Package: targeter
Type: Package
Title: target automated profiling
Version: 0.1
Author: WeLoveDataScience
Maintainer: Eric Lecoutre <eric.lecoutre@welovedatascience.com>
Description: Describes a target (binary/nominal/continuous) by crossing
    it with many candidate explanatory variables. Generates aggregated statistics
    allowing to prioritize inspection, such as Information Value.
    We also provide plot method and a report generation engine.
    Package is aimed at exloring big data, both in terms of records or variables.
License: file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: 
     R (>= 3.5),
     data.table
RoxygenNote: 7.2.0
NeedsCompilation: no
Imports:
     assertthat,
     ggplot2,
     gridExtra,
     scales,
     ggrepel,
     knitr,
     rmarkdown,
     kableExtra
Suggests:
     clustering.sc.dp,
     Ckmeans.1d.dp,
     flextable
